● CATEGORY 1: HEADER SECTIONS (3 Files)
WHY Header Sabse Important Hai?
Customer jab website kholta hai:
→ Sabse PEHLE header dikhta hai
→ Navigation YAHAN se hoti hai
→ Search, Cart, Account — sab YAHAN hai
→ Agar header broken = POORI SITE unusable
FILE 1: header-group.json
Kya Hai? Yeh ek JSON file hai jo header ke saare sections ko ek group mein rakhta hai.

Kyun Chahiye?

Problem:  Header mein 3 alag sections hain (custom, announcements, main header)
          Har page pe inhe individually add karna = tedious + inconsistent

Solution: Ek GROUP banao — sab pages pe automatically same header aaye
Structure:

{
  "type": "header",
  "name": "Header Group",
  "sections": {
    "custom": {
      "type": "custom",
      "settings": {}
    },
    "announcements": {
      "type": "header-announcements",
      "settings": {}
    },
    "header": {
      "type": "header",
      "settings": {}
    }
  },
  "order": ["custom", "announcements", "header"]
}
Connection Map:

header-group.json
    │
    ├──→ sections/custom.liquid          (Custom announcement bar)
    ├──→ sections/header-announcements.liquid  (Default announcements)
    └──→ sections/header.liquid          (Main header)
    
    ↑ Called by: layout/theme.liquid
      {% sections 'header-group' %}
IF-THEN Logic:

IF:   header-group.json se koi section hataao
THEN: Woh section har page se gayab ho jaayega

IF:   order array change karo
THEN: Header sections ka sequence badal jaayega
      (e.g., announcements header ke neeche aa jaaye)

IF:   header-group.json delete karo
THEN: Poora header har page se gayab — CRITICAL ERROR
